# Lesson interactive challenges

When creating or editing steps in `shared/lessons/` that are **interactive challenges** (`challenge` or `challengeSequence`):

- **Define in the lesson file.** Interactive challenges are described by **FEN positions** plus `challenge` or `challengeSequence` (and optional `postChallenge`) directly in the lesson. There are no separate design documents.
- **Verify.** Confirm the FEN and every move are legal (e.g. on [lichess.org/analysis](https://lichess.org/analysis)); if multiple moves are correct, use `challenge: [move1, move2]`.
- **Validate and play-through.** Run `npm run validate:lessons` and complete the challenge as a learner.

See [LESSON_AUTHORING.md — Interactive Challenges](LESSON_AUTHORING.md#interactive-challenges) and [Describing interactive challenges](LESSON_AUTHORING.md#describing-interactive-challenges).
